Social Media Do's and Don'ts Checklist

✅ Do's (Best Practices)

Enable Privacy Settings: Regularly review and restrict who can see your personal posts and contact information.
Think Before You Post: Consider if your content is professional and how it might be perceived by future employers or faculty.
Fact-Check Information: Verify the authenticity of news or academic resources before sharing them with your batchmates.
Network Professionally: Use platforms like LinkedIn to connect with industry experts and alumni in your field.
Respect Others' Privacy: Always ask for permission before posting photos or tagging friends in your digital content.
❌ Don'ts (Avoid These)

Don't Share Sensitive Data: Never post your home address, phone number, or official ID details on public profiles.
Don't Engage in Cyberbullying: Avoid using offensive language or participating in online arguments and harassment.
Don't Click Suspicious Links: Avoid clicking on "clickbait" or unverified links that could lead to phishing sites.
Don't Plagiarize Content: Never claim someone else's digital work, art, or writing as your own without proper credit.
Don't Over-Share Location: Avoid posting real-time "check-ins" that reveal your exact location to strangers.
